## Pre-Installation Steps

Before creating a backup account, you have to install CDP backup agent on the server and configure the backup server IP address in it. Open the CDP port 1167 in the firewall to allow incoming and outgoing connections. 

- How to install r1soft CDP agent on Linux server

## Monitor The Remote Account Available Licenses

You will also have to keep watching for number of available licenses. And from time to time remove any cancelled servers from r1soft. You will have to remove DiskSafe, user, Server and volume in same order.

Usually we use 2 methods to find out any server which is possibly cancelled.

- Under Volumes, look for the volumes with space in MBs in column "On disk size", for example in "volumes list" christra-64-235-57-92 have "on disk size" only 6.1 MB, it mean this client's server have no backup. so possibly server is cancelled
- Secondly from Dash board, look for Failed policies, mostly backups fail if customer server is reinstalled or cancelled. Check the physical server linked to that policy. 
Also check the alerts of that failed policy to get the exact reason. 
If policy failed due to Disk Quota error or Agent connection failed or any errors, then make sure if the physical server is active or not. If it is active then contact customer about this issue. If it not active then delete the policy, disk safe, user, server and volume linked to that server.
